d a secession from Plymouth colony <i>c.</i> 1627 and founded the settlement that became Salem, MA. He was probably the son of Christopher Connant, who came over from England aboard the <i>Anne</i> in 1623."],"variants":[{"name":"Canant","meanings":["Altered form of English   Conant  ."]},{"name":"Conan","meanings":["English and Scottish (of Breton origin): from the Old Breton personal name <i>Conan</i>, the name of Breton chiefs, kings, and of a saint, itself from British Celtic <i>Cunagnos</i>, a derivative of <i>cuno-</i> ‘hound’. This was one of the Breton names introduced to England at the Norman Conquest in 1066 and was common among tenants of the Richmond fee in Lincolnshire and Yorkshire. Compare   Conant  ."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705182,"age":9,"year":"1066","julianDay":2110409,"title":"Battle of Hastings","description":"Battle of Hastings was fought between the Norman-French army and the battle-wary English army on October 14, 1066. Duke William of Normandy believed he was the rightful king rather than Harold, who had been crowned king several months earlier. Harold was killed in battle and William was crowned king on Christmas Day 1066.","url":"https://www.english-heritage.org.uk/learn/1066-and-the-norman-conquest/what-happened-battle-hastings/","urlTitle":"English Heritage - Battle of Hastings","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705183,"age":29,"year":"1086","julianDay":2117714,"title":"Domesday Book","description":"Domesday Book is Britain's earliest extant public record with information containing land surveys and landholdings commissioned by William I. The book was completed in 1086.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/domesday/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Domesday","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705184,"age":39,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Nonant had at least 1 son with Robert fitz Martin. She died in 1175, in Totnes, Devon, England."},"et":{"–1175":"–1175","1080–1159":"1080–1159","1135–1209":"1135–1209","1080":"1080","abt 1159":"umbes 1159","1159":"1159","1135":"1135","1066":"1066","1175":"1175","1086":"1086","about 1135":"umbes 1135","1096":"1096","1209":"1209","Totnes, Devon, England":"Totnes, Devon, England","Dartington, Devon, England":"Dartington, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Nevern Castle, Pembroke, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Pembroke, Pembrokeshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–1175":"–1175","1080–1159":"1080–1159","1135–1209":"1135–1209","1080":"1080","abt 1159":"noin 1159","1159":"1159","1135":"1135","1066":"1066","1175":"1175","1086":"1086","about 1135":"noin 1135","1096":"1096","1209":"1209","Totnes, Devon, England":"Totnes, Devon, England","Dartington, Devon, England":"Dartington, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Nevern Castle, Pembroke, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Pembr